text.tspan: iwlist scan » search for wireless networks
sudo command » execute a command as root
sudo -i » open a console as root
Ctrl+R » look for a command in the user
Ctrl+C » terminate any command in execution
Alt+F2 » execute command in graphic mode
xkill » kill a client its x resource
apt-get update » refresh the update list
aptitude show pkg » show package "pkg" info
cd ~ » go to user home directory
cd - » go to directory previously accessed
cd .. » change directory to parent directory
ls -a » list all files, including hidden
touch file » create a new empty file "file"
-t : show a list of contained files
-f : with -c create file with the same name
